Description: cast the desktop to Wi-Fi Display sinks and Chromecast
 GNOME Network Displays streams the desktop to remote displays using the
 Wi-Fi Display (Miracast) protocol or to Chromecast devices.
 .
 It uses the mutter screencast portal when available and falls back to X11
 frame grabbing otherwise, and can stream audio via a dedicated PulseAudio
 sink.
